  "sections": {
    "Background": {
      "text": "Self-limiting inflammatory process of the hip\nMost common cause of acute hip pain in children <10yr\nPeak incidence 3-8yrs, with a mean of 6 yrs\nMale:Female is 2:1\nUsually unilateral\n32-50% present after recent viral URI\nPossible posttraumatic or allergic pathologies",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": []
    },
    "Clinical_Features": {
      "text": "Abrupt onset of unilateral hip pain, limp, and restricted hip motion\nNontoxic appearance\nMay have a low grade fever",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": []
    },
    "Differential_Diagnosis": {
      "text": "",
